n\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:SittingBull.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/SittingBull.jpg/18px-SittingBull.jpg\" width=\"18\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/SittingBull.jpg/27px-SittingBull.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/SittingBull.jpg/36px-SittingBull.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"530\" data-file-height=\"880\" /></a></td><td><i>This article relating to the <a href=\"/wiki/Indigenous_peoples_of_the_Americas\" title=\"Indigenous peoples of the Americas\">Indigenous peoples of the Americas</a> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Sipapu&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\" style=\"position: absolute; right: 15px; display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:NorthAm-native-stub\" title=\"Template:NorthAm-native-stub\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:NorthAm-native-stub\" title=\"Template talk:NorthAm-native-stub\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:NorthAm-native-stub&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><br />\nThe Hopi and other Pueblo Culture people (Zuni, Acoma) believe that they are born of the Grand Canyon which is where the original Sipapu is located.  The Grand Canyon is the 'place of emergence' and each modern Hopi village would have one or several kivas.  Each kiva is subterranean and contains a small hole, just off center, to represent their place of emergence for religious purpose.\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit rep